title: Box, 19th century
creditline: Gift of Mr. and Mrs. Arthur Wiesenberger
description: Small box, rectangular in plan, oval in section.  Hinged lid, thinly veneered lining of shell. Painted geometric design on top, black lines with green, blue, red, and white filled areas.

tombstone.epitaph:
Box, 19th century.
19th century. Wood (possibly olivewood), painted decoration. Gift of Mr. and Mrs. Arthur Wiesenberger. 1967-66-49.
